 made\n|-\n| [[Kirk Hinrich]] || 1,049\n|-\n| [[Ben Gordon]] || 770\n|-\n| [[Scottie Pippen]] || 664\n|-\n| [[Michael Jordan]] || 555\n|-\n| [[Steve Kerr]] || 430\n|-\n| [[Andr\u00e9s Nocioni]] || 403\n|-\n| [[Luol Deng]] || 387\n|-\n| ''[[Nikola Miroti\u0107]]'' || 363\n|-\n| [[Toni Kuko\u010d]] || 351\n|-\n| ''[[Derrick Rose]]'' || 350\n|}\n{{columns-end}}\n\n==Head coaches==\n{{Main|List of Chicago Bulls head coaches}}\n\n==Hall of Famers, retired and honored numbers==\n===Basketball Hall of Famers===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"5\" style=\"{{NBA color cell|Chicago Bulls}};\"|Chicago Bulls Hall of Famers\n|-\n! colspan=\"5\" style=\"text-align:center; {{NBA color cell2|Chicago Bulls}};\"|Players\n|-\n! No. || Name || Position || Tenure || Inducted\n|-\n| '''42''' || [[Nate Thurmond]] || [[Center (basketball)|C]] || 1974\u20131976 || 1985\n|-\n| '''8''' || [[George Gervin]] || [[Shooting guard|G]]/[[Small forward|F]] || 1985\u20131986 || 1996\n|-\n| '''00''' || [[Robert Parish]] || [[Center (basketball)|C]] || 1996\u20131997 || 2003\n|-\n| '''23'''<br />'''45''' || [[Michael Jordan]] <sup>1</sup> || [[Shooting guard|G]] || 1984\u20131993<br />1995\u20131998 || 2009\n|-\n| '''33''' || [[Scottie Pippen]] <sup>2</sup> || [[Small forward|F]] || 1987\u20131998<br />2003\u20132004 || 2010\n|-\n| '''53''' || [[Artis Gilmore]] || [[Center (basketball)|C]] || 1976\u20131982<br />1987 || 2011\n|-\n| '''91''' || [[Dennis Rodman]] || [[Small forward|F]] || 1995\u20131998 || 2011\n|-\n| '''25''' || [[Chet Walker]] || [[Small forward|F]] || 1969\u20131975 || 2012\n|-\n| '''5''' || [[Guy Rodgers]] || [[Point guard|G]] || 1966\u20131967 || 2014\n|-\n! colspan=\"5\" style=\"text-align:center; {{NBA color cell2|Chicago Bulls}};\"|Coaches\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\"|Name || Position || Tenure || Inducted\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\"|[[Phil Jackson]] <sup>6</sup> || [[Head coach|Coach]] || 1989\u20131998 || 2007\n|-\n| '''4''' || [[Jerry Sloan]] <sup>3</sup> || [[Head coach|Coach]] || 1979\u20131982 || 2009\n|-\n! colspan=\"5\" style=\"text-align:center; {{NBA color cell2|Chicago Bulls}};\"|Contributors\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\"|Name || Position || Tenure || Inducted\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\"|[[Jerry Colangelo]] <sup>4</sup> || \u2013 || 1968\u20131995 || 2004\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\"|[[Jerry Reinsdorf]] || Owner || 1985\u2013present || 2016\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\"|[[Jerry Krause]] || General manager || 1985\u20132003 || 2017\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\"|[[Rod Thorn]] <sup>5</sup> || General manager || 1978\u20131985 || 2018\n|}\n'''Notes:'''\n* <sup>1</sup> In total, Jordan was inducted into the Hall of Fame twice \u2013 as player and as a member of the [[1992 United States men's Olympic basketball team|1992 Olympic team]].\n* <sup>2</sup> In total, Pippen was inducted into the Hall of Fame twice \u2013 as player and as a member of the [[1992 United States men's Olympic basketball team|1992 Olympic team]].\n* <sup>3</sup> He also played for the team in 1966\u20131976.\n* <sup>4</sup> Colangelo worked as a marketing director, scout, and assistant to the president of the team.<ref>{{cite web|last=Charles |first=Mike |title=Jerry's story |url=http://www.jcolangelo.com/jerrys-story.php?&page=2 |accessdate=August 16, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120314223509/http://www.jcolangelo.com/jerrys-story.php?&page=2 |archivedate=March 14, 2012}}</ref>\n* <sup>5</sup> He also coached the team in 1981\u20131982.\n* <sup>6</sup> Also served as assistant coach in 1987\u20131989.\n\n===FIBA Hall of Famers===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"5\" style=\"{{NBA color cell|Chicago Bulls}};\"|Chicago Bulls Hall of Famers\n|-\n! colspan=\"5\" style=\"text-align:center; {{NBA color cell2|Chicago Bulls}};\"|Players\n|-\n! No. || Name || Position || Tenure || Inducted\n|-\n| '''23'''<br />'''45''' || [[Michael Jordan]] || [[Guard (basketball)|G]] || 1984\u20131993<br />1995\u20131998 || 2015 <br /> & 2017 as member of 1992 Dream Team\n|-\n| '''33''' || [[Scottie Pippen]] || [[Forward (basketball)|F]] || 1987\u20131998 || 2017 <br /> as member of 1992 Dream Team\n|-\n| '''7''' || [[Toni Kuko\u010d]] || [[Forward (basketball)|F]] || 1993\u20132000 || 2017\n|}\n\n===Chicagoland Sports Hall of Fame===\n{{Main|Chicagoland Sports Hall of Fame}}\n\n===Retired numbers and honorees===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"{{NBA color cell|Chicago Bulls}};\"|'''Chicago Bulls retired numbers and honorees'''\n|-\n! style=\"{{NBA color cell2|Chicago Bulls}};\"|No.\n! style=\"{{NBA color cell2|Chicago Bulls}};\"|Player\n! style=\"{{NBA color cell2|Chicago Bulls}};\"|Position/charge\n! style=\"{{NBA color cell2|Chicago Bulls}};\"|Tenure\n! style=\"{{NBA color cell2|Chicago Bulls}};\"|Date retired\n|-\n| '''4''' ||{{sortname|Jerry|Sloan}} || [[Guard (basketball)|G]]/[[Small forward|SF]] || 1966\u20131976 || {{Dts|1978|February|17|format=mdy}}\n|-\n| '''10''' || {{sortname|Bob|Love}} || [[Power forward (basketball)|F]] || 1968\u20131976 || {{Dts|1994|January|14|format=mdy}}\n|-\n| '''23''' || {{sortname|Michael|Jordan}} || [[Shooting guard|SG]] || 1984\u20131993<br>1995\u20131998 || {{Dts|1994|November|1|format=mdy}}\n|-\n| '''33''' || {{sortname|Scottie|Pippen}} || [[Small forward|SF]] || 1987\u20131998<br>2003\u20132004 || {{Dts|2005|December|9|format=mdy}}\n|-\n|\u2014|| {{sortname|Phil|Jackson}} || Coach || 1987\u20131989 (assistant)<br />1989\u20131998 (head) || {{Dts|1999|May|5|format=mdy}}\n|-\n|\u2014|| {{sortname|Johnny|Kerr}} || Coach<br />Business manager<br />Broadcaster || 1966\u20131968 (head coach)<br />1973\u20131975 (business manager)<br />1977\u20132009 (broadcaster)\n|{{Dts|2009|February|10|format=mdy}}\n|-\n|\u2014|| {{sortname|Jerry|Krause}} || General manager || {{Dts|1985|3|26}}\u2013{{Dts|2003|4|7}} || {{Dts|2003|October|31|format=mdy}}\n|}\n\n==Media==\n{{Main|List of Chicago Bulls broadcasters}}\n\n===Radio===\nThe team's games are broadcast on [[Entercom]]'s [[WSCR]] (670) as of February 3, 2018. From October 2015-January 2018, games were carried on [[Cumulus Media]]'s [[WLS (AM)|WLS]] (890) in a deal that was expected to last until the 2020\u201321 season, but was nullified in the middle of the 2017\u201318 season after Cumulus filed for [[Chapter 11 bankruptcy]] and nullified several large play-by-play and talent contracts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.csnchicago.com/chicago-bulls/white-sox-bulls-announce-long-term-deals-wls-am-890|title=White Sox, Bulls Announce Long-Term Deals with WLS AM 890|last=CSN Staff|first=|date=July 16, 2015|website=|publisher=CSNChicago.com|accessdate=October 26, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.robertfeder.com/2018/01/31/done-deal-bulls-pivot-score/|title=Done deal: Bulls pivot to The Score|last=Feder|first=Robert|date=January 31, 2018|publisher=[[Robert Feder]]|accessdate=February 1, 2018}}</ref>\n\n[[Chuck Swirsky]] does play-by-play, with [[Bill Wennington]] providing [[color commentary]]. [[Univision Radio]]'s [[WRTO (AM)|WRTO]] (1200) has carried [[Spanish language]] game coverage since 2009\u201310, with Omar Ramos as play-by-play announcer and Matt Moreno as color analyst.\n\n===Television===\nThe Bulls' television broadcasts are televised by [[NBC Sports Chicago]], which broadcasts all of the games that are not televised nationally as of the [[2019-20 Chicago Bulls season|2019-20 season]]. For many years, broadcasts were split between NBC Sports Chicago (and prior to that, [[FSN Chicago]]), [[WGN-TV]], and [[WCIU-TV]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Chicago Bulls Schedule|url=https://www.nba.com/bulls/schedule/|publisher=NBA Media Ventures, LLC|website=Bulls.com|accessdate=June 29, 2018}}</ref> The announcers are [[Neil Funk]] and [[Stacey King]].\n\nOn January 2, 2019, the Bulls (along with the [[Chicago White Sox]] and [[Chicago Blackhawks]]) agreed to an exclusive multi-year deal with NBC Sports Chicago, ending the team's broadcasts on WGN-TV following the 2018\u201319 season.<ref>{{cite news|title=NBC Sports Chicago Announces New Pact With White Sox, Bulls, and Blackhawks|url=https://www.nbcchicago.com/news/sports/nbc-sports-chicago-announces-new-deal-with-white-sox-bulls-and-blackhawks-503802931.html|date=January 2, 2019|publisher=WMAQ-TV|accessdate=January 4, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Chicago Bulls}}\n* {{Official website}}\n\n{{Chicago Bulls}}\n{{Navboxes|titlestyle = {{NBA color cell|Chicago Bulls|border=2}}|list =\n{{Chicago Bulls seasons}}\n{{NBA}}\n{{Chicagosports}}\n{{Illinois Sports}}\n}}\n{{Portal bar|Sports|Chicago|Illinois}}\n\n[[Category:Chicago Bulls| ]]\n[[Category:National Basketball Association teams]]\n[[Category:Basketball teams in Chicago|Bulls]]\n[[Category:Basketball teams established in 1966]]\n[[Category:1966 establishments in Illinois]]\n", "name_user": "Batweirdo2020", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chicago_Bulls"}
{"title_page": "Antonio Mac\u00edas del Real", "text_new": "{{infobox person\n|name=Antonio Mac\u00edas del Real\n|image=Maciasdelreal1897.jpg\n|caption=Mac\u00edas del Real in 1897\n|birth_date= 1866 \n|birth_place=[[Madrid]], {{ESP}} \n|death_date={{death year and age|1939|1866}}\n|death_place=[[Buenos Aires]], {{ARG}}\n|occupation=writer, pharmacist\n}}\n\n'''Antonio Mac\u00edas del Real''' (1866\u20131939) was a Spanish writer and pharmacist that moved to [[Guatemala]] where he wrote for most prestigious cultural publications.  Among his articles are those that we wrote for ''[[La Ilustraci\u00f3n Guatemalteca]]'' during the last year of general [[Jos\u00e9 Mar\u00eda Reina Barrios]] presidency.  When the president was assassinated on 8 February 1898, Mac\u00edas del Real wrote ''Perfiles biogr\u00e1ficos de don [[Manuel Estrada Cabrera]]'' (''Biographical profiles of Mr. Manuel Estrada Cabrera'',<ref name=macias>{{harvnb|Mac\u00edas del Real|1898|p=}}</ref> who had been appointed as interim President; Macias del Real kept writing on behalf of the new president since then. In 1902 his adulation paid off, as Estrada Cabrera granted him the Pacific Railroad concession.  According to Guatemalan historian [[Rafael Ar\u00e9valo Mart\u00ednez]] in his book ''\u00a1Ecce Pericles!'', Mac\u00edas del Real -a pharmacist graduated from Universidad Central de Madrid and later incorporated in Guatemala<ref name=madrid>{{harvnb|Ministerio de Educaci\u00f3n, Cultura y Deportes de Espa\u00f1a|28 May 2015|p=}}</ref>- was the one that gave Estrada Cabrera a potent venom that the latter used to get rid of his opponents.<ref name=martinez44>{{harvnb|Ar\u00e9valo Mart\u00ednez|1945|p=44}}</ref>\n\n== Biography ==\n{{Location map many| Guatemala\n|AlternativeMap=Relief map of Guatemala.jpg\n|border=black\n|caption=Stations and stretches of the Panamerican Railroad that had been given in concession to Mac\u00edas del Real in 1902.\n<div style=\"-moz-column-count:2; column-count:2;\">\n# Vado Ancho, [[Pajapita]], [[San Marcos Department|San Marcos]]\n#[[Coatepeque, Quetzaltenango|Coatepeque]], [[Quetzaltenango Department|Quetzaltenango]]\n# Caballo Blanco, [[Retalhuleu Department|Retalhuleu]]\n# Las Cruces, [[Retalhuleu Department|Retalhuleu]]\n</div>\n | label=1| position=top|bg=white|label_size=70\n      | lat=14.716667| long=-92.016667\n | label2=2| pos2=top|bg2=white|label2_size=70\n      | lat2=14.699685| long2=-91.865131\n | label3=3| pos3=bottom | bg3=white|label3_size=70\n      | lat3=14.507877| long3=-91.848857\n | label4=4|label4_size=70\n      | pos4=bottom| bg4=white\n      | lat4=14.523955| long4=-91.694148\n | width=260 | float=right\n}}\n\nMac\u00edas del Real got his doctorate in Pharmacy in Universidad Central de Madrid in 1894, with a dissertation about the pharmaceutical studies of ''Eucaliptus gl\u00f3bulus''<ref name=madrid/> and he was incorporated into the College of Medicine and Pharmacy of [[University of San Carlos of Guatemala|Universidad Nacional]] in Guatemala on 3 July 1896.<ref name=Asturias330>{{harvnb|Asturias|1902|p=330}}</ref>\n\nBetween 1896 and 1897 he wrote regularly for the ''[[La Ilustraci\u00f3n Guatemalteca]]'' where he worked alongside writer and public speaker [[Rafael Spinola]] and with the Guatemalan photography pioneer [[Alberto G. Valdeavellano]].  His articles were mainly about political and cultural issues.{{sfn|Mac\u00edas del Real|1896|P=}}{{sfn|Mac\u00edas del Real|15 February 1897|p=}}{{sfn|Mac\u00edas del Real|1897|p=}}{{sfn|Mac\u00edas del Real|1 August 1897|p=}}\n\nOn 18 April 1902, given his then excellent relationship with president [[Manuel Estrada Cabrera]], he was granted the concession to build and operate the Panamerican Railroad between Las Cruces and Vado-Ancho; however, he could not build the railway until [[Coatepeque, Quetzaltenango|Coatepeque]] and had to sell his rights to the Central Railroad Company.{{sfn|Chavarr\u00eda Smeaton|1970|p=4}} The original contract with Mac\u00edas del Real had been extremely generous and had been signed by the lieutenant secretary of Economy, Jos\u00e9 Flamenco and approved by Estrada Cabrera; the contract authorized the exclusivity on the construction and usage of the railroad for twenty four years, counting from the moment the section was open to the public.{{sfn|Estrada Paniagua|1908|p=24}} Besides, Mac\u00edas del Real and his descendants would have enjoyed the revenue from the railway for 99 years, after which the line was supposed to go back to the State of Guatemala.{{sfn|Estrada Paniagua|1908|p=25}}\n\n== See also ==\n* {{Portal-inline|Guatemala}}\n* {{Portal-inline|Biography}}\n* [[Manuel Estrada Cabrera]]\n* [[La Ilustraci\u00f3n Guatemalteca]]\n* [[Rafael Spinola]]\n\n== Notes and references ==\n\n=== Notes ===\n{{reflist|group=Nota}}\n\n=== References ===\n{{reflist}}\n\n===Bibliography ===\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite book|last=Ar\u00e9valo Mart\u00ednez|first=Rafael|authorlink=Rafael Ar\u00e9valo Mart\u00ednez|title=\u00a1Ecce Pericles!|publisher=Tipograf\u00eda Nacional|location=Guatemala|url=https://www.scribd.com/doc/190285559/Arevalo-Martinez-Ecce-Pericles#scribd|year=1945|language=Spanish|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Asturias|first=Francisco|title=Historia de la medicina en Guatemala|url=https://archive.org/details/historiadelamed00astugoog|year=1902|publisher=Tipograf\u00eda Nacional|location=Guatemala|language=Spanish|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Chavarr\u00eda Smeaton|first=Francisco Antonio|year=1970|title=Problem\u00e1tica urban\u00edstica de los ferrocarriles en la Ciudad de Guatemala y an\u00e1lises para su soluci\u00f3n en el \u00e1rea metropolitana|location=Guatemala|publisher=Facultad de Arquitectura de la Universidad de San Carlos de Guatemala|url=http://biblioteca.usac.edu.gt/tesis/02/02_0044.pdf|language=Spanish|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Estrada Paniagua|first=Felipe|year=1908|title=Recopilaci\u00f3n de Leyes de Guatemala, 1902-1903|location=Guatemala|publisher=Arturo S\u00edguere y C\u00eda.|url=https://archive.org/details/recopilacinde21unseguat|volume=XXI|language=Spanish|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal|last=Mac\u00edas del Real|first=A.|title=Revista quincenal|journal=La Ilustraci\u00f3n Guatemalteca|location=Guatemala|year=1896|volume=I|issue=2|url=https://archive.org/stream/ilustracionguate00guat#page/46/mode/2up|language=Spanish|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal|last=Mac\u00edas del Real|first=A.|authormask=1|title=Revista quincenal|journal=La Ilustraci\u00f3n Guatemalteca|location=Guatemala|date=15 February 1897|volume=I|issue=14|url=https://archive.org/stream/ilustracionguate00guat#page/348/mode/2up|language=Spanish|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal|last=Mac\u00edas del Real|first=A.|authormask=1|year=1897|title=El Arzobispo Ricardo Casanova y Estrada|journal=La Ilustraci\u00f3n Guatemalteca|url=https://archive.org/stream/ilustracionguate00guat#page/325/mode/2up|location=Guatemala|volume=I|issue=17|publisher=S\u00edguere, Guirola y C\u00eda|language=Spanish|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal|last=Mac\u00edas del Real|first=A.|authormask=1|title=Resumen Quincenal|date=1 August 1897|volume=II|issue=25|journal=La Ilustraci\u00f3n del Pac\u00edfico|url=https://archive.org/details/lailustra225unseguat|location=Guatemala|publisher=Siguere, Guirola y C\u00eda|language=Spanish|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal|last=Mac\u00edas del Real|first=A.|authormask=1|title=Resumen Quincenal|date=1 August 1897|volume=II|issue=27|journal=La Ilustraci\u00f3n del Pac\u00edfico|url=https://archive.org/details/lailustra225unseguat|location=Guatemala|publisher=Siguere, Guirola y C\u00eda|language=Spanish|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Mac\u00edas del Real|first=A.|authormask=1|title=Perfiles biogr\u00e1ficos de don Manuel Estrada Cabrera, presidente de la Rep\u00fablica de Guatemala|url=https://archive.org/details/perfilesbiogrfi00realgoog|publisher=El Dem\u00f3crata|year=1898|location=Guatemala|language=Spanish|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite web|author=Ministerio de Educaci\u00f3n, Cultura y Deporte de Espa\u00f1a|title=Archivo de Antonio Mac\u00edas del Real|url=http://pares.mcu.es/ParesBusquedas/servlets/Control_servlet?accion=3&&txt_tipo_busqueda=dl&txt_busqueda=&txt_correo=S&txt_id_desc_ud=4509190|journal= [[Portal de Archivos Espa\u00f1oles]] |location=Espa\u00f1a|date=28 May 2015|accessdate=28 May 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150528231452/http://pares.mcu.es/ParesBusquedas/servlets/Control_servlet?accion=3&&txt_tipo_busqueda=dl&txt_busqueda=&txt_correo=S&txt_id_desc_ud=4509190|archivedate=28 May 2015|language=Spanish|ref=harv}}\n{{refend}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Macias del Real, Antonio}}\n[[Category:Manuel Estrada Cabrera]]\n[[Category:1866 births]]\n[[Category:1939 deaths]]\n[[Category:Date of birth missing]]\n[[Category:Date of death missing]]\n[[Category:Spanish male writers]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriates in Argentina]]\n", "text_old": "{{infobox person\n|name=Antonio Mac\u00edas del Real\n|image=Maciasdelreal1897.jpg\n|caption=Mac\u00edas del Real in 1897\n|birth_date= 1866 \n|birth_place=[[Madrid]], {{ESP}} \n|death_date={{death year and age|1939|1866}}\n|death_place=[[Buenos Aires]], {{ARG}}\n|occupation=writer, pharmacist\n}}\n\n'''Antonio Mac\u00edas del Real''' (1866\u20131939) was a Spanish writer and pharmacist that moved to [[Guatemala]] where he wrote for most prestigious cultural publications.  Among his articles are those that we wrote for ''[[La Ilustraci\u00f3n Guatemalteca]]'' during the last year of general [[Jos\u00e9 Mar\u00eda Reina Barrios]] presidency.  When the president was assassinated on 8 February 1898, Mac\u00edas del Real wrote ''Perfiles biogr\u00e1ficos de don [[Manuel Estrada Cabrera]]'' (''Biographical profiles of Mr. Manuel Estrada Cabrera'',<ref name=macias>{{harvnb|Mac\u00edas del Real|1898|p=}}</ref> who had been appointed as interim President; Macias del Real kept writing on behalf of the new president since then. In 1902 his adulation paid off, as Estrada Cabrera granted him the Pacific Railroad concession.  According to Guatemalan historian [[Rafael Ar\u00e9valo Mart\u00ednez]] in his book ''\u00a1Ecce Pericles!'', Mac\u00edas del Real -a pharmacist graduated from Universidad Central de Madrid and later incorporated in Guatemala<ref name=madrid>{{harvnb|Ministerio de Educaci\u00f3n, Cultura y Deportes de Espa\u00f1a|28 May 2015|p=}}</ref>- was the one that gave Estrada Cabrera a potent venom that the latter used to get rid of his opponents.<ref name=martinez44>{{harvnb|Ar\u00e9valo Mart\u00ednez|1945|p=44}}</ref>\n\n== Biography ==\n{{Location map many| Guatemala\n|AlternativeMap=Relief map of Guatemala.jpg\n|border=black\n|caption=Stations and stretches of the Panamerican Railroad that had been given in concession to Mac\u00edas del Real in 1902.\n<div style=\"-moz-column-count:2; column-count:2;\">\n# Vado Ancho, [[Pajapita]], [[San Marcos Department|San Marcos]]\n#[[Coatepeque, Quetzaltenango|Coatepeque]], [[Quetzaltenango Department|Quetzaltenango]]\n# Caballo Blanco, [[Retalhuleu Department|Retalhuleu]]\n# Las Cruces, [[Retalhuleu Department|Retalhuleu]]\n</div>\n | label=1| position=top|bg=white|label_size=70\n      | lat=14.716667| long=-92.016667\n | label2=2| pos2=top|bg2=white|label2_size=70\n      | lat2=14.699685| long2=-91.865131\n | label3=3| pos3=bottom | bg3=white|label3_size=70\n      | lat3=14.507877| long3=-91.848857\n | label4=4|label4_size=70\n      | pos4=bottom| bg4=white\n      | lat4=14.523955| long4=-91.694148\n | width=260 | float=right\n}}\n\n\nMac\u00edas del Real got his doctorate in Pharmacy in Universidad Central de Madrid in 1894, with a dissertation about the pharmaceutical studies of ''Eucaliptus gl\u00f3bulus''<ref name=madrid/> and he was incorporated into the College of Medicine and Pharmacy of [[University of San Carlos of Guatemala|Universidad Nacional]] in Guatemala on 3 July 1896.<ref name=Asturias330>{{harvnb|Asturias|1902|p=330}}</ref>\n\nBetween 1896 and 1897 he wrote regularly for the ''[[La Ilustraci\u00f3n Guatemalteca]]'' where he worked alongside writer and public speaker [[Rafael Spinola]] and with the Guatemalan photography pioneer [[Alberto G. Valdeavellano]].  His articles were mainly about political and cultural issues.{{sfn|Mac\u00edas del Real|1896|P=}}{{sfn|Mac\u00edas del Real|15 February 1897|p=}}{{sfn|Mac\u00edas del Real|1897|p=}}{{sfn|Mac\u00edas del Real|1 August 1897|p=}}\n\nOn 18 April 1902, given his then excellent relationship with president [[Manuel Estrada Cabrera]], he was granted the concession to build and operate the Panamerican Railroad between Las Cruces and Vado-Ancho; however, he could not build the railway until [[Coatepeque, Quetzaltenango|Coatepeque]] and had to sell his rights to the Central Railroad Company.{{sfn|Chavarr\u00eda Smeaton|1970|p=4}} The original contract with Mac\u00edas del Real had been extremely generous and had been signed by the lieutenant secretary of Economy, Jos\u00e9 Flamenco and approved by Estrada Cabrera; the contract authorized the exclusivity on the construction and usage of the railroad for twenty four years, counting from the moment the section was open to the public.{{sfn|Estrada Paniagua|1908|p=24}} Besides, Mac\u00edas del Real and his descendants would have enjoyed the revenue from the railway for 99 years, after which the line was supposed to go back to the State of Guatemala.{{sfn|Estrada Paniagua|1908|p=25}}\n\n== See also ==\n* {{Portal-inline|Guatemala}}\n* {{Portal-inline|Biography}}\n* [[Manuel Estrada Cabrera]]\n* [[La Ilustraci\u00f3n Guatemalteca]]\n* [[Rafael Spinola]]\n\n== Notes and references ==\n\n=== Notes ===\n{{reflist|group=Nota}}\n\n=== References ===\n{{reflist}}\n\n===Bibliography ===\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite book|last=Ar\u00e9valo Mart\u00ednez|first=Rafael|authorlink=Rafael Ar\u00e9valo Mart\u00ednez|title=\u00a1Ecce Pericles!|publisher=Tipograf\u00eda Nacional|location=Guatemala|url=https://www.scribd.com/doc/190285559/Arevalo-Martinez-Ecce-Pericles#scribd|year=1945|language=Spanish|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Asturias|first=Francisco|title=Historia de la medicina en Guatemala|url=https://archive.org/details/historiadelamed00astugoog|year=1902|publisher=Tipograf\u00eda Nacional|location=Guatemala|language=Spanish|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Chavarr\u00eda Smeaton|first=Francisco Antonio|year=1970|title=Problem\u00e1tica urban\u00edstica de los ferrocarriles en la Ciudad de Guatemala y an\u00e1lises para su soluci\u00f3n en el \u00e1rea metropolitana|location=Guatemala|publisher=Facultad de Arquitectura de la Universidad de San Carlos de Guatemala|url=http://biblioteca.usac.edu.gt/tesis/02/02_0044.pdf|language=Spanish|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Estrada Paniagua|first=Felipe|year=1908|title=Recopilaci\u00f3n de Leyes de Guatemala, 1902-1903|location=Guatemala|publisher=Arturo S\u00edguere y C\u00eda.|url=https://archive.org/details/recopilacinde21unseguat|volume=XXI|language=Spanish|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal|last=Mac\u00edas del Real|first=A.|title=Revista quincenal|journal=La Ilustraci\u00f3n Guatemalteca|location=Guatemala|year=1896|volume=I|issue=2|url=https://archive.org/stream/ilustracionguate00guat#page/46/mode/2up|language=Spanish|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal|last=Mac\u00edas del Real|first=A.|authormask=1|title=Revista quincenal|journal=La Ilustraci\u00f3n Guatemalteca|location=Guatemala|date=15 February 1897|volume=I|issue=14|url=https://archive.org/stream/ilustracionguate00guat#page/348/mode/2up|language=Spanish|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal|last=Mac\u00edas del Real|first=A.|authormask=1|year=1897|title=El Arzobispo Ricardo Casanova y Estrada|journal=La Ilustraci\u00f3n Guatemalteca|url=https://archive.org/stream/ilustracionguate00guat#page/325/mode/2up|location=Guatemala|volume=I|issue=17|publisher=S\u00edguere, Guirola y C\u00eda|language=Spanish|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal|last=Mac\u00edas del Real|first=A.|authormask=1|title=Resumen Quincenal|date=1 August 1897|volume=II|issue=25|journal=La Ilustraci\u00f3n del Pac\u00edfico|url=https://archive.org/details/lailustra225unseguat|location=Guatemala|publisher=Siguere, Guirola y C\u00eda|language=Spanish|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal|last=Mac\u00edas del Real|first=A.|authormask=1|title=Resumen Quincenal|date=1 August 1897|volume=II|issue=27|journal=La Ilustraci\u00f3n del Pac\u00edfico|url=https://archive.org/details/lailustra225unseguat|location=Guatemala|publisher=Siguere, Guirola y C\u00eda|language=Spanish|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Mac\u00edas del Real|first=A.|authormask=1|title=Perfiles biogr\u00e1ficos de don Manuel Estrada Cabrera, presidente de la Rep\u00fablica de Guatemala|url=https://archive.org/details/perfilesbiogrfi00realgoog|publisher=El Dem\u00f3crata|year=1898|location=Guatemala|language=Spanish|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite web|author=Ministerio de Educaci\u00f3n, Cultura y Deporte de Espa\u00f1a|title=Archivo de Antonio Mac\u00edas del Real|url=http://pares.mcu.es/ParesBusquedas/servlets/Control_servlet?accion=3&&txt_tipo_busqueda=dl&txt_busqueda=&txt_correo=S&txt_id_desc_ud=4509190|journal= [[Portal de Archivos Espa\u00f1oles]] |location=Espa\u00f1a|date=28 May 2015|accessdate=28 May 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150528231452/http://pares.mcu.es/ParesBusquedas/servlets/Control_servlet?accion=3&&txt_tipo_busqueda=dl&txt_busqueda=&txt_correo=S&txt_id_desc_ud=4509190|archivedate=28 May 2015|language=Spanish|ref=harv}}\n{{refend}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Macias del Real, Antonio}}\n[[Category:Manuel Estrada Cabrera]]\n[[Category:1866 births]]\n[[Category:1939 deaths]]\n[[Category:Date of birth missing]]\n[[Category:Date of death missing]]\n[[Category:Spanish male writers]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriates in Argentina]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antonio_Mac%C3%ADas_del_Real"}
{"title_page": "SecureDataRecovery", "text_new": "{{multiple issues|\n{{advert|date=April 2013}}\n{{notability|Companies|date=April 2013}}\n{{third-party|date=April 2013}}\n}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Secure Data Recovery Services\n| logo = Secure Data Recovery logo.jpg\n| type = Privately held\n| parent=\n| foundation = 1997\n| founder=\n| location_city = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]]\n| location_country = United States\n| key_people =\n| industry = [[Data recovery]]\n| area_served       =  Worldwide\n| products =\n| revenue =\n| net_income =\n| num_employees =\n| subsid =\n| homepage = [http://www.securedatarecovery.com www.securedatarecovery.com]\n| footnotes =\n}}\n\n'''Secure Data Recovery Services''' is a privately held company with corporate headquarters in [[California]], which provides [[data recovery]] services. Secure Data Recovery Services was the first data recovery company to achieve [[Statement on Auditing Standards No. 70: Service Organizations#Proposed changes to SAS 70|SSAE 16 Type II]] certification.<ref>[http://www.securedatarecovery.com/ssae-16-data-recovery.html SSAE 16 Type II Certification<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120107042448/http://www.securedatarecovery.com/ssae-16-data-recovery.html |date=2012-01-07 }}</ref> The SSAE 16 Type II Certification is an updated version of the [[Statement on Auditing Standards No. 70: Service Organizations|SAS 70 standards]], which the company had also previously held.  SSAE 16 reports (also known as \"SOC 1\" reports) retain the original purpose of SAS 70 by providing a means of reporting on the system of internal control particularly as it relates to internal control over financial reporting (ICFR).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ssae16professionals.com/services/ssae-16-soc1/|title=SSAE 16 (SOC 1) Overview}}</ref> It is also the only company in the data recovery industry to have a certified [[Cleanroom|Class 10 ISO 4 Cleanroom]].<ref>[http://www.securedatarecovery.com/data-recovery-clean-room.html Class 10 ISO 4 Cleanroom<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130317163300/http://www.securedatarecovery.com/data-recovery-clean-room.html |date=2013-03-17 }}</ref> They are also certified to perform data recovery by [[Hitachi]], [[Seagate Technology|Seagate]], [[IBM]], [[Toshiba]], [[Maxtor]], [[Fujitsu]], [[Lacie]], and other hard drive manufacturers.<ref>[http://www.securedatarecovery.com/data-recovery-services.html Data Recovery Services: Retrieve Data with Data Recovery Services<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120104090947/http://www.securedatarecovery.com/data-recovery-services.html |date=2012-01-04 }}</ref> \n\n==History==\nSecure Data Recovery Services was founded in 1997, and it was incorporated in 2007 in Los Angeles, California. Its main lab and SSAE 18 Type II certified research center are located in Los Angeles, but the company also has more than 300 receiving service centers located all around the mainland United States.\n\n==Security certifications==\nIn September 30, 2011, Secure Data Recovery Services became the first company from the [[data recovery]] sector to be awarded the Statement on Standards for Attestation Engagements (SSAE) 16 Type II Certification.<ref>[http://www.securedatarecovery.com/ssae-16-data-recovery.html SSAE 16 Certified Data Recovery by Secure Data Recovery Services<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120107042448/http://www.securedatarecovery.com/ssae-16-data-recovery.html |date=2012-01-07 }}</ref> The SSAE 16 Type II is given by the [[American Institute of Certified Public Accountants]]. SSAE / SSA certifications became important for data handlers after the passage of [[Sarbanes\u2013Oxley Act|Sarbanes\u2013Oxley Act of 2002]].\n\nSecure Data Recovery Services is [[McAfee]] Secured and tested daily.<ref>[https://www.mcafeesecure.com/RatingVerify?ref=www.securedatarecovery.com McAfee SECURE | www.securedatarecovery.com<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> The privacy statement is validated and approved by the [[TRUSTe]] Organization.<ref>[http://privacy.truste.com/ctv/validation?url=www.securedatarecovery.com Secure Data Recovery Services's policies for online privacy and online safety are certified by TRUSTe<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> It is also verified by [[VeriSign]].<ref>[https://trustsealinfo.verisign.com/splash?form_file=fdf/splash.fdf&dn=www.securedatarecovery.com&lang=en VeriSign Trust Seal<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20121217220026/https://trustsealinfo.verisign.com/splash?form_file=fdf/splash.fdf&dn=www.securedatarecovery.com&lang=en |date=2012-12-17 }}</ref> Secure Data Recovery is one of the few data recovery companies to have Extended Validation SSL on its site.<ref>[https://seal.godaddy.com/verifySeal?sealID=m30rvwsd9zRE81F4TTGEtQwShIBeB9z0Kadl07ejJvDErbln5bkNvyd92RP Secure Site by GoDaddy.com<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n\nIn October 2, 2017, Company  earn SSAE 18 SOC 2 Type II & SOC 3 certifications. <ref>[https://www.securedatarecovery.com/certifications/ssae-18 SSAE 18 SOC 2 Type II & SOC 3 Certified | www.securedatarecovery.com]</ref>\n\n==Partner certifications==\nSecure Data Recovery is a certified partner of [[Intel]],<ref>[http://software.intel.com/partner/search-detail?companyguid=da138cb7-9032-e211-a774-005056b20261 Intel Registered Partner: Secure Data Recovery<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> [[Lenovo]],<ref>[http://www.securedatarecovery.com/certified-secure-data-recovery.html Certified Secure Data Recovery Services - Choose the Right Data Recovery Company<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120107022712/http://www.securedatarecovery.com/certified-secure-data-recovery.html |date=2012-01-07 }}</ref> [[IBM]], [[NortonLifeLock|Symantec]], and [[AMD]], as well as a Gold Certified partner of [[Microsoft]].<ref>[http://www.microsoft.com/hk/certpartner/default.mspx Microsoft Certified Partner<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Other major certified partners include Seagate, AMD, Iomega, Dell, Symantec, VMware, and HP.\n\n==Awards and achievements==\nSecure Data Recovery Services is a member of ACRBO, the Association of Computer Repair Business Owners. It is also a member within the IEEE, ISSA and PPA Member and, over the years, the company website has posted over one hundred customer testimonial letters.<ref>[http://www.securedatarecovery.com/data-recovery-customers.html Secure Data Recovery Customer Testimonial Letters<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130127003102/http://www.securedatarecovery.com/data-recovery-customers.html |date=2013-01-27 }}</ref>\n\nIn May 2011, Secure Data Recovery were granted a rating of A by the [[Better Business Bureau]].<ref>[http://www.la.bbb.org/business-reviews/Computer-Repair-and-Disaster-Recovery/Secure-Data-Recovery-Services-in-Los-Angeles-CA-100105582 Secure Data Recovery Services Business Review in Los Angeles, CA<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>  In 2012, [[TopTenReviews]] rated Secure Data Recovery Services with 10 out of 10 points for its features, security, recovery capabilities, and help and support. The website awarded Secure Data Recovery Services the TopTenREVIEWS Gold Award <ref>[http://raid-recovery-review.toptenreviews.com/secure-data-recovery-review.html Secure Data Recovery Services Review from Top Ten Reviews<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> for RAID data recovery companies.\n\n==See also==\n\n* [[Computer forensics]]\n* [[Error detection and correction]]\n* [[List of data recovery software]]\n* [[Statements on auditing standards]]\n* [[Sarbanes\u2013Oxley Act]]\n* [[List of data recovery companies]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|https://www.securedatarecovery.com}}\n*[https://www.securedatarecovery.com/blog/ Company Blog]\n\n[[Ca